<TEXT>
 Rep. <PERSON> Barney </PERSON> <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> is offering an apology to political supporters and assuring them that `` my judgment has improved'' since his involvement with a male prostitute. `` I made some serious mistakes in judgment several years ago. What I did was wrong,'' the <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> Democrat, said in a letter mailed Friday to home-state supporters and volunteers in his previous campaigns for <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. `` It did not affect my public decisions or any public business,'' <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> wrote. `` But I regret that some of my past personal actions are troubling to people who placed their confidence in me.'' <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> also drew some Republican support Friday for his decision not to resign while awaiting an inquiry by the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> ethics committee into his 18-month relationship with <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gobie </PERSON>. `` He deserves a fair hearing,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Newt </PERSON> <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Georgia </LOCATION>, the House Republican whip. <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON>, who is under investigation by the ethics committee over his personal finances in a book deal, told reporters it was appropriate for <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> to await the panel's findings. <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> is a five-term congressman and outspoken liberal who was re-elected overwhelmingly in 1988 after disclosing the year before that he is homosexual. <PERSON> Gobie </PERSON> has charged he operated a prostitution ring out of <PERSON> Frank </PERSON>'s Capitol Hill apartment <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> has acknowledged paying <PERSON> Gobie </PERSON> for sex and then hiring him as a personal assistant and driver, but says he threw <PERSON> Gobie </PERSON> out when he learned of the prostitution operation. That was shortly before <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> publicly disclosed he is homosexual. <PERSON> Frank </P