<HEAD>Sunbather Slain as Wife Looks On</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A nude sunbather was gunned down at a secluded beach by an attacker demanding drugs, jolting this sleepy tourist area where random violence is rare. <PERSON> Phillip </PERSON> <PERSON> Bogdanoff </PERSON>, 49, was lying on a beach blanket with his wife Thursday afternoon when two men approached the couple and demanded marijuana, <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Barbara </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> sheriff's Sgt. <PERSON> Jan </PERSON> <PERSON> Bullard </PERSON> said. When <PERSON> Bogdanoff </PERSON> said he had none, one of the men shot him twice in the head, killing him, Ms. <PERSON> Bullard </PERSON> said. Both men fled and remain at large, police said. <PERSON> Bogdanoff </PERSON>'s wife, <PERSON> Diana </PERSON>, 41, was not attacked. Nudity did not appear to figure as a motive in the killing, Ms. <PERSON> Bullard </PERSON> said. `` There were no sexual overtones,'' she said. `` Nothing more to it. Just a random, violent act.'' The slaying at the beach about 20 miles up the coast from this seaside city, which is 75 miles northwest of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, alarmed residents. `` We do n't expect this kind of thing to happen around here,'' Ms. <PERSON> Bullard </PERSON> said. `` It woke up a sleepy county.''
