<HEAD>With PM-Obit-Berlin Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> <PERSON> Berlin </PERSON>'s songs were so much a part of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> for generations that it would be hard to think of life without him, his admirers said. `` There'll never be another <LOCATION> Irving </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION>. It's an era that's gone,'' said opera singer <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Merrill </PERSON>, who also sings <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION>'s `` He wrote songs for the people,'' <PERSON> Merrill </PERSON> said. `` He was not a great musician but he had a great ear and he had a feeling for melody and words that was precious.'' <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION>, whose most memorable compositions included `` White Christmas,'' `` Easter Parade'' and `` God Bless <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>,'' died Friday night at his home at the age of 101. Cabaret singer <PERSON> Bobby </PERSON> <PERSON> Short </PERSON> said he thought <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> would be remembered as `` a very, very, very important, very great American composer. He is perhaps the last of the giants _ and I think that's not a bad way to go. `` His musicality was constantly astonishing. People who thought they could pin down the <LOCATION> Irving </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> style would be surprised to find his newest song a complete turnabout,'' <PERSON> Short </PERSON> said. Actress-dancer <PERSON> Ginger </PERSON> <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON> paid tribute to <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> by humming a phrase from his `` Cheek to Cheek.'' `` I'm in heaven,'' she sang sadly in a telephone interview from her home in Eagle Point, Ore. Breaking off to describe the thrill of working with <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Astaire </PERSON> on the movie `` Top Hat,'' she said: `` It was like heaven.'' Miss <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON> recalled the songwriter's kindness when she was first breaking into show business. `` I went into his music company to get some songs,'' she sai