<TEXT>
 Police have arrested a young man in connection with the fatal shooting of <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Budd </PERSON>, father of track star <PERSON> Zola </PERSON> <PERSON> Budd </PERSON>, officers said today. Police said they found a shotgun and pickup truck which were missing from <PERSON> Budd </PERSON>'s farmhouse when they arrested the 24-year-old man Friday night in <LOCATION> Welkom </LOCATION>, 60 miles north of the farm near <LOCATION> Bloemfontein </LOCATION>. Police did not identify the man, but the independent <ORGANIZATION> South </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> African </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> said he was expected to appear in court Monday on a charge of murder. Newspapers said today that police had been seeking a young man who had been doing construction work on the farm, where <PERSON> Budd </PERSON>'s body was found Friday. Police said the 56-year-old retired printer had two shotgun wounds in the left side of his body when it was found in the bedroom of a house he built on the farm of a friend. Ms. <PERSON> Budd </PERSON> and her father did not communicate in recent years and he did not attend his daughter's April 15 wedding in <LOCATION> Bloemfontein </LOCATION>, saying he had not been invited. `` I do n't know what to say. What can a person say?'' Ms. <PERSON> Budd </PERSON> said upon learning of her father's death Friday ngith. <PERSON> Budd </PERSON> was divorced from Ms. <PERSON> Budd </PERSON>'s mother. <PERSON> Zola </PERSON> <PERSON> Budd </PERSON> rose to prominence as a frail, barefooted teen-ager who broke a string of South African and world records. Many sports fans remember her collision with <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> runner <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Decker </PERSON> during the 3,000-meter run in the 1984 Olympics in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Decker </PERSON>, the favorite, was knocked out of the race, while 