the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> slid several months ago when the British expelled 11 Soviet journalists and diplomats on complaints of spying and the Soviets retaliated by expelling 11 Britons. But the <ORGANIZATION> Tass </ORGANIZATION> news agency said today: `` In <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> diplomatic circles, it is believed that these differences should not be viewed as an obstacle to the development of relations between the two nations.''
