<HEAD>Minor Temblor Shakes Los Angeles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A slight temblor jolted downtown <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> on Saturday about two hours after another minor quake shook an area east of the city, but no injuries or damages were reported. `` The ceiling shook a little bit and the desks shook a few seconds,'' said <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> sheriff's spokesman Deputy <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Mosely </PERSON>. The afternoon earthquake measured 2.4 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale, said Hall Daily of the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Technology </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Pasadena </LOCATION>. Its epicenter was about three miles north of downtown and six miles south-southwest of <LOCATION> Pasadena </LOCATION>, he said. About two hours earlier, a quake measuring 2.9 on the Richer scale shook an area about 55 miles east of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, near <LOCATION> Rialto </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bernardino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, Daily said. The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an earthquake as measured by ground motion recorded on a seismograph. Every increase of one number on the scale means that the ground motion is 10 times greater. A quake of magnitude 2 is the smallest normally felt by humans. A quake of magnitude 3.5 can cause slight damage in populated areas.
